<paragraph blockId="7.[151,552,1669,1729]" box="[151,457,1704,1729]" pageId="7" pageNumber="208">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,228,1704,1729]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1853,1875]" captionTargetBox="[247,1326,215,1779]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[205,1373,193,1811]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. Adults in dorsal and ventral views. Taxon names appear below each set. Bia actorion actorion: a, male, Guyana, Kartabo (CMNH); b, female, Guyana, Two Hat Mountain, E Kanukus S Rupununi (USNM). Bia actorion ecuatoria DeVries &amp; Penz, new ssp.: c, male holotype, Ecuador, Sucumbios, Garza Cocha (PJD); d, female paratype, Ecuador, Sucumbios, Garza Cocha (PJD). Bia actorion occulta Casagrande &amp; Penz, new ssp.: e, male holotype, Brazil, Pará, Acará (DZUP); f, female paratype, Brazil, Pará, Sto Antonio do Tauá (DZUP). Intermediate between actorion and decaerulea: g, male, Suriname (RMNH); h, male, Suriname, Coronie (RMNH)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/569732/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="208">Figs 3</figureCitation>
