<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="209" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,431]" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,313,298,323]" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">Remarks.</emphasis>
Some male specimens from Guyana and Suriname (Appendix) seem to be intermediate between 
<taxonomicName box="[151,244,336,359]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Bia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="actorion">
<emphasis box="[151,244,336,359]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">actorion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[296,418,335,359]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Bia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decaerulea">
<emphasis box="[296,418,335,359]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">decaerulea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having a wide dorsal forewing orange band and iridescent band markedly smaller than the typical 
<taxonomicName box="[234,327,371,394]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Bia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="actorion">
<emphasis box="[234,327,371,394]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">actorion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[343,410,370,395]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1853,1875]" captionTargetBox="[247,1326,215,1779]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[205,1373,193,1811]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. Adults in dorsal and ventral views. Taxon names appear below each set. Bia actorion actorion: a, male, Guyana, Kartabo (CMNH); b, female, Guyana, Two Hat Mountain, E Kanukus S Rupununi (USNM). Bia actorion ecuatoria DeVries &amp; Penz, new ssp.: c, male holotype, Ecuador, Sucumbios, Garza Cocha (PJD); d, female paratype, Ecuador, Sucumbios, Garza Cocha (PJD). Bia actorion occulta Casagrande &amp; Penz, new ssp.: e, male holotype, Brazil, Pará, Acará (DZUP); f, female paratype, Brazil, Pará, Sto Antonio do Tauá (DZUP). Intermediate between actorion and decaerulea: g, male, Suriname (RMNH); h, male, Suriname, Coronie (RMNH)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/569732/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[396,410,371,395]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="3.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" unit="g" value="3.0">3</quantity>
</figureCitation>
g, h). Some specimens may have a somewhat truncated valva tip, which is more commonly found in 
<taxonomicName box="[249,371,407,431]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Bia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decaerulea">
<emphasis box="[249,371,407,431]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">decaerulea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Investigating the possibility of hybridization between these taxa would be worthwhile.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
